(0, 1, 'Stage Entertainment/Media', 1, 'Media, entertainment', 'Sint-Katelijnestraat 28', 'Brussel', 'Belgium', '2013-05-01', '2013-08-01', '<p>As an <strong>intern</strong> from our editorial department, your job is to manage the textual and visual content of our website to help the campaigns for e-marketing, to cheer and help maintain and assist in the Facebook page a hand formatting newsletters.</p>', '<p><strong>Management textual content of the website Cadeaubox.be</strong> (descriptive texts and related information about partners) write explanatory texts or translations on hotels, restaurants, etc. Depending on the mother tongue: in French or Dutch. ; Management visual content of the website Cadeaubox.be (photos of partners) Working in the back office for the update of the products, managing Community (Facebook page pimp, Twitter, etc.)</p>', 'Bachelor', '3e'),
(1, 1, 'Graphic designer', 1, 'Media, entertainment', 'Watermolenstraat 95', 'Machelen ', 'Belgium', '2013-05-12', '2013-06-26', '<p>As a Graphic Designer, you will help to implement the Clear2Pay corporate style (look and feel) throughout the global marketing collateral; from flyers, brochures and white papers to adverts, banners and booth material, HTML-mailings, PowerPoint presentations and website content. You will help to build the Clear2Pay website in a new CMS. You will work together with the graphic designer and copywriter to answer the global marketing/sales and presales needs for marketing materials.</p>', '<p>Good knowledge of Adobe graphical software tools: Illustrator, Photoshop and InDesign.; Knowledge of Microsoft Office tools: PowerPoint, Excel, Word, etc. Some knowledge of website development languages: HTML, CSS, etc. Good communication skills, social contact, team player and service minded.;Fluent in English (speaking &amp; writing), knowledge of Dutch &amp; French is a plus. ;Able to work independently and to take up actions proactively.</p>', 'Bachelor', '3e'),
(3, 1, 'Webdesign + SEO', 1, 'IT', 'Brusselsestraat 23', 'Londerzeel', 'Belgium', '2013-05-02', '2013-07-09', '<ul>\r\n<li>Optimization of link building.</li>\r\n<li>Establish dedicated webpages</li>\r\n<li>Documenting and updating corporate website</li>\r\n</ul>', '<p>Training IT / web design with knowledge of SEO, website usability and link building.</p>', 'Master', '2e'),
(4, 0, 'Development Chemist-Summer', 1, 'Chemistry, pharmacy', '40 Rue Etienne Marcel', 'Paris', 'France', '2013-05-03', '2013-07-05', '<p>013 Summer Internship: Development Chemist Successful candidates will conduct independent research projects that are linked to larger studies of watersheds, streams, estuary, marshes, or tidal creeks. In addition, participants are expected to assist principal investigators, postdocs, research assistants, and graduate students with ongoing projects and gain experience in a variety of research areas related to coastal science. REU participants are expected to collect and analyze data and present their research results in oral presentations and in poster and written formats by the end of their fellowship. Accommodations are provided at the field station during field work studies.</p>', '<p>Studying for BS/MS/PHD in chemistry or related discipline, having<strong> completed at least freshman year</strong>.<br />Experience in working in lab environment<br />Evidence of independently analyzing data and generating follow-up experiments.<br />Track record of team participation and working with cross functional teams desired.<br />Exceptional verbal and written communication skills.</p>', 'Master', '1e'),
(5, 2, 'Education Internship Summer', 1, 'Education', '53-64 Chancery Ln', 'London', 'England', '2013-04-13', '2014-04-13', '<p>Duties include implementing, marketing and creating educational programing and events. Working closely with the Education Manager in organizing materials and set up and break down of events. Assist with large group tours and interpretation of Museum. Applicants must work well with children and adults as well as be able to do some lifting. \r\nInterns enjoy a variety of museum experiences, including exhibits, programs, special events, interaction with visitors, and working with a professional staff. Hours and schedules are to be arranged with individual interns and departments. These internships are unpaid, however, credit may be accrued depending on each intern''s individual school policy</p>', '<p>Interns must have a reliable source of transportation to the Museum. Interns must be available on Sundays</p>', 'Bachelor', '3e'),
(6, 2, 'Educational Research Internship', 1, 'Education', 'Ifflandstrasse 1', 'Berlin', 'Germany', '2013-04-15', '2013-09-22', '<p><span style="color: #333333; font-family: ''Open Sans'', sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 16px;">Gillis Educational Consulting, LLC is a boutique consulting firm providing an array of services and products. We are currently looking for two bright college students to help us develop our internal research department. As an Educational Research Intern with our company, you will do much to help our internal and external operations and programming. For those interested in gaining real world work experience, developing vital skills in research, and giving back to the community, this internship opportunity may be for you!&nbsp;</span></p>', '<p>Research will be done in the following topics: \n\n1. Early childhood education and development \n2. Technology in education \n3. Societal factors affecting educational procedures \n4. Education disparities among minority populations \n5. Educational policy and law \n\nAssignments will involve (but are not limited to): \n\n- Literature searches \n- Abstract production \n- Conducting and transcribing industry interviews \n- Writing blog posts for company website \n- Attending educational events in the Washington, D.C. area<p>\n', 'Master', '2e'),
(7, 2, 'Marketing Intern', 1, 'Media, entertainment', '139-144 Pearse St', 'Dublin', 'Ireland', '2013-05-14', '2013-12-25', '<p><span style="color: #333333; font-family: ''Open Sans'', sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 16px;">Wantickets.com is one of the leading online nightlife ticketing companies in North America. Our ticketing solutions reach hundreds of thousands of unique visitors on a monthly basis. In 2011, Wantickets joined the River North network of marketing agencies, which is based in Chicago, Illinois.&nbsp;</span><br style="color: #333333; font-family: ''Open Sans'', sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 16px;" /><br style="color: #333333; font-family: ''Open Sans'', sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 16px;" /><span style="color: #333333; font-family: ''Open Sans'', sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 16px;">Wantickets provides ticketing services for a variety of events; ranging from nightclubs, standing room venues, concerts and festivals, to conventions and trade shows. Through our live events, online nightlife ticketing, and exclusive partnerships, Wantickets has positioned itself as one of the leading gateways to the trendsetter marketplace. Wantickets.com prides itself on having a personal connection with its audience&rsquo;s unique nightlife taste. We offer a community of music and lifestyle events to an audience&nbsp;</span><a id="_GPLITA_0" style="color: #0099d1; font-weight: bold; font-family: ''Open Sans'', sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 16px;" title="Click to Continue &gt; by Browse to Save" href="http://www.internships.com/posting/Marketing-Intern-I2499102">seeking</a><span style="color: #333333; font-family: ''Open Sans'', sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 16px;">&nbsp;new entertainment experiences.</span></p>', '<h3 style="margin: 10px 0px 5px; font-family: ''Open Sans Condensed'', sans-serif; line-height: 1em; color: #333333; text-rendering: optimizelegibility; font-size: 21px;"><span style="fon